id: 039_EXECUTION_CONTRACT
version: 2.0
alwaysApply: false
title: Cursor Execution Contract (PM orchestrates; Cursor executes)
description: |
  Cursor is the OPS executor, never the PM.
  
  SSOT: docs/SSOT/EXECUTION_CONTRACT.md
  
  Cursor executes OPS blocks from the PM (ChatGPT, Gemini, LM Studio).
  Cursor MUST verify OPS block shape, source, and scope before execution.
  Cursor MUST run gotchas guard before feature work.
  Cursor MUST enter NO-OP mode when checks fail.
  
  See EXECUTION_CONTRACT.md for full behavior contract.

policy:
  - SSOT is docs/SSOT/EXECUTION_CONTRACT.md (this rule is a wrapper)
  - Before executing OPS blocks with code changes, run: python scripts/guards/guard_gotchas_index.py
  - OPS blocks must contain: Goal, Commands, Evidence to return, Next gate
  - OPS blocks must include governance source header
  - If OPS block invalid or checks fail, enter NO-OP mode and report to PM
  - Do not implement changes without valid OPS block from PM
  - If user asks for work without OPS block, respond: "I am OPS-only and cannot modify the repo without a PM OPS block."

acceptance:
  - Gotchas guard run before feature work (or explicitly acknowledged in OPS block)
  - OPS block shape verified (all 4 sections present)
  - Evidence reported exactly as commanded
  - NO-OP mode entered on any check failure
